# Sliding Window Pattern – Complete Notes

---

## What is Sliding Window?

Sliding Window ek algorithmic technique hai jisme hum **array ya string ke contiguous (continuous) part** par kaam karte hain.

Instead of har subarray/substring ko alag-alag calculate karna (O(n²)), hum ek **window** banate hain jo gradually **slide** karti hai → overall complexity **O(n)** ho jaati hai.

---

## When to Use Sliding Window?

Use this pattern when:

* Question me **subarray / substring / continuous** likha ho
* Maximum / Minimum / Longest / Shortest nikalna ho
* Range dynamically change ho rahi ho

 Non-contiguous problems me Sliding Window use nahi hota.

---

## Types of Sliding Window

###  Fixed Size Sliding Window

* Window ka size pehle se fixed hota hai (k)
* Example: "Maximum sum subarray of size k"

###  Variable Size Sliding Window

* Window ka size condition par depend karta hai
* Example: "Longest substring without repeating characters"

---

## Core Intuition (Golden Rule)

```
Right pointer → window expand karta hai
Left pointer  → window shrink karta hai (jab condition break ho)
```

---

## Fixed Size Sliding Window – Template (C#)

```csharp
int windowSum = 0;
int maxSum = int.MinValue;
int k = 3;

for (int i = 0; i < nums.Length; i++)
{
    windowSum += nums[i];

    if (i >= k - 1)
    {
        maxSum = Math.Max(maxSum, windowSum);
        windowSum -= nums[i - (k - 1)];
    }
}
```

---

## Variable Size Sliding Window – Template (C#)

```csharp
int left = 0;
Dictionary<char, int> map = new Dictionary<char, int>();

for (int right = 0; right < s.Length; right++)
{
    // expand window

    while (condition breaks)
    {
        // shrink window
        left++;
    }

    // update answer
}
```

---

## Common Mistakes 

1. Left pointer move karna bhool jana
2. Window shrink galat time pe karna
3. Condition galat likhna (<=, >= confusion)
4. HashMap update ka order galat hona

---

## Pattern Recognition Tip (Interview Ready)

Agar question bole:

> "Find longest / shortest / maximum / minimum subarray or substring"

Turant socho → **Sliding Window**

